You are working in the JUDIAgent repository.

Canonical project guidance lives in `AGENTS.md`. Cursor-specific always-on
rules live in `.cursor/rules/`. This file is a short fallback summary for older
Cursor setups.

- Use the project environment: `uv sync`, then `uv run ...`.
- Preserve public entry points: `examples/agent.py`,
  `examples/autonomous_agent.py`, and `langgraph.json`.
- Keep library code under `src/judiagent/`; keep `examples/` thin.
- Treat `src/judiagent/rag/`, `src/judiagent/prompts.py`, and vendored
  `src/judiagent/rag/judi/` material as behavior-sensitive.
- Keep real secrets only in local `.env`; never write keys into tracked files.
- Avoid destructive git or filesystem operations unless explicitly requested.
- On PACE/shared clusters, use login nodes for git/lint/smoke tests and compute
  nodes for heavy Julia/JUDI setup or live agent runs.
